ip utility, iproute2-6.17.0, libbpf 1.6.2
  
  ip
  Mostra / manipula roteamento, dispositivos, roteamento baseado em p√≥liticas e t√∫neis.  Alguns subcomandos como `address` t√™m suas p≈ïoprias documenta√ß√µes de uso.  Mais informa√ß√µes: https://manned.org/ip.8.
  - Lista interfaces com informa√ß√µes detalhadas:    ip address
  - Lista interfaces com breves informa√ß√µes sobre a camada de rede:    ip -brief address
  - Lista interfaces com breves informa√ß√µes sobre a camada de link de dados:    ip -brief link
  - Exibe a tabela de roteamento:    ip route
  - Mostra vizinhos (ARP tabela):    ip neighbour
  - Ativa / desativa uma interface:    sudo ip link set interface up|down
  - Adiciona / remove um endere√ßo de IP a uma interface:    sudo ip address add|delete ip/mask dev interface
  - Adiciona uma rota padr√£o:    sudo ip route add default via ip dev interface


  
ss utility, iproute2-6.17.0
  
  ss
  Utility to investigate sockets.  More information: https://manned.org/ss.
  - Show all TCP/UDP/RAW/UNIX sockets:    ss --all -t|-u|-w|-x
  - Filter TCP sockets by states, only/exclude:    ss state|exclude bucket|big|connected|synchronized|...
  - Show all TCP sockets connected to the local HTTPS port (443):    ss --tcp src :443
  - Show all TCP sockets listening on the local 8080 port:    ss --listening --tcp src :8080
  - Show all TCP sockets along with processes connected to a remote SSH port:    ss --processes --tcp dst :ssh
  - Show all UDP sockets connected on specific source and destination ports:    ss --udp 'sport == :source_port and dport == :destination_port'
  - Show all TCP IPv4 sockets locally connected on the subnet 192.168.0.0/16:    ss --ipv4 --tcp src 192.168/16
  - Kill IPv4 or IPv6 Socket Connection with a specific destination IP and port:    ss --kill dst ip_address dport = port



  
tc utility, iproute2-6.17.0, libbpf 1.6.2
  
  tc
  Show/manipulate traffic control settings.  More information: https://manned.org/tc.
  - Add constant network delay to outbound packages:    sudo tc qdisc add dev eth0 root netem delay delay_in_millisecondsms
  - Add normal distributed network delay to outbound packages:    sudo tc qdisc add dev eth0 root netem delay mean_delay_msms delay_std_msms
  - Add package corruption/loss/duplication to a portion of packages:    sudo tc qdisc add dev eth0 root netem corruption|loss|duplication effect_percentage%
  - Limit bandwidth, burst rate and max latency:    sudo tc qdisc add dev eth0 root tbf rate max_bandwidth_mbmbit burst max_burst_rate_kbkbit latency max_latency_before_drop_msms
  - Show active traffic control policies:    tc qdisc show dev eth0
  - Delete all traffic control rules:    sudo tc qdisc delete dev eth0
  - Change traffic control rule:    sudo tc qdisc change dev eth0 root netem policy policy_parameters



  
bridge utility, 6.17.0
  bridge
  Show and manipulate network bridge addresses and devices.  More information: https://manned.org/bridge.
  - List all bridges and their interfaces:    bridge link
  - Show port vlan information:    bridge vlan
  - Assign a VLAN to a port:    sudo bridge vlan add dev lanX vid vlan_id pvid tagged|untagged
  - Remove a VLAN from a port:    sudo bridge vlan delete dev lanX vid vlan_id
  - Watch for changes in bridge interfaces:    bridge monitor
  - Display help:    bridge help



  
rtmon utility, iproute2-6.17.0
  
  rtmon
  Save network state changes to a file.  More information: https://manned.org/rtmon.
  - Save all network state changes to a file:    sudo rtmon file path/to/file
  - Specify the type of change to log:    sudo rtmon file link|address|route




  
nstat utility, iproute2-6.17.0
  
  nstat
  View network statistics.  More information: https://manned.org/nstat.
  - View network statistics since last time [3mnstat[23m was run:    nstat
  - View all-time network statistics:    nstat --ignore
  - Display help:    nstat --help




